# Tabbed Section Shell Pattern

- For any section page that contains tabs, use a dedicated `*-shell.component` as the parent container.
- The shell component owns:
  - title bar layout and actions
  - title-bar dropdowns/selection state
  - tab selection/index and tab-level routing concerns
  - loading orchestration for cross-tab page context
- Child tab components own:
  - tab-specific UI and form logic
  - tab-specific data load/save flows unless explicitly shared
- Avoid mixing shell responsibilities into tab child components and avoid tab-form logic in the shell.

## Naming Convention

- Parent container: `<section>-shell.component`
- Main tab content component: `<section>.component` (or explicit tab feature name)

## Example

- `maintenance-shell.component` = title bar + property/office selectors + tab group
- `maintenance.component` = Maintenance tab content logic/UI
